
[1]merger

   MERG'ER, n. [L. mergo, to merge.] In law, a merging or drowning of a
   less estate in a greater; as when a reversion in fee simple descends to
   or is purchased by a tenant of the same estate for years, the term for
   years is merged, lost, annihilated in the inheritance or fee simple
   estate.
